Description: Fragment of a clay seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The fragment is showing two seal impression of an oval scarab-like seal. Only the part with the seal impression has survived. The back of the sealing shows a small part with an uneven surface that is quite blurred but could show impressions of a wall (?) The clay shows voids of organic impressions and mica. The two seal impressions are underneath each other, they are shallow and blurry, showing an uraeus facing to the left, followed by a falcon, followed by another uraeus followed by another falcon with a sun disc and a flagellum. Above the first falcon another unidentified sign, maybe a boat? The same impression can be seen on EA86960 and EA86893.
